theorem closure_eq_univ_of_P1_and_dense_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A →
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) →
    closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  intro hP1 hDense
  -- First, `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)` thanks to `P1`.
  have hSub : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := by
    have : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (closure (interior (A : Set X))) :=
      closure_mono hP1
    simpa [closure_closure] using this
  -- Hence `closure A ⊆ univ`.
  have hSubUniv : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [hDense] using hSub
  -- Conversely, `univ ⊆ closure A` because `interior A ⊆ A`.
  have hUnivSub : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    intro x _
    -- `x` lies in `closure (interior A)` by density.
    have hx : (x : X) ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := by
      simpa [hDense]
    -- Monotonicity of `closure` yields the desired membership.
    have hMono : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A)
    exact hMono hx
  -- Assemble the two inclusions.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm hSubUniv hSubUniv.symm

theorem closure_nonempty_of_nonempty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    (A : Set X).Nonempty → (closure (A : Set X)).Nonempty := by
  intro hA
  rcases hA with ⟨x, hx⟩
  exact ⟨x, subset_closure hx⟩
